Huawei has launched two new Watch GT wearables at an event in Paris. The company announced two new variants of the Watch GT: the Watch GT Active and the Watch GT Elegant. These new smartwatches are available in 46mm and 42mm sizes, and sport new designs while retaining the core features of the original device. This means that they will still have extremely good battery life in addition to 1.39-inch OLED displays. Huaweiâ€™s Watch GT Active and Elegant editions also have the same functionality as the original model, such as a heart rate monitor, Bluetooth connectivity, GPS connectivity, 128MB of storage, and 16MB of RAM. At the time of writing, local pricing listed online for the Watch GT was: No pricing for the Elegant model was available. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-300604" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-Watch-GT-Active-46mm.jpg" alt="Huawei Watch GT Active 46mm" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-Watch-GT-Active-46mm.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-Watch-GT-Active-46mm-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/03/Huawei-Watch-GT-Active-46mm-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Jamie McKane is reporting from Paris as a guest of Huawei.